      '<h2 style=\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; outline: none; font-family: Quicksand, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; line-height: 30px; color: rgb(59, 66, 73); font-size: 20px; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(247, 248, 249); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\\">About this listing</h2><p>Wilkommen bei edelweiss!&nbsp;</p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><strong style="font-weight:normal;" id="docs-internal-guid-4b9a4639-7fff-958e-a335-7abac1253f64"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;">&nbsp;The perfect Alpine retreat awaits you in the heart of the Last Frontier. A cozy private bedroom and a Bavarian-style master loft share an open, perfectly appointed cottage with a cozy kitchen and living room with a single bathroom made for escaping city life and embracing the peace of the arctic forest, minutes away from the Talkeetna airport, and a short stroll into the Village, or a very short drive, if your legs are tired from all the hiking, snowshoeing, x-country skiing, river rafting, fishing, flight-seeing glacier trips, float-plane flying and all the gateway to Denali, has to offer. Just a short stroll from the Talkeetna stop on the Alaska Railroad if you want to save the drive but with parking big enough for your Alaska truck pulling seasonal toys.</span></strong></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><strong style="font-weight:normal;" id="docs-internal-guid-4b9a4639-7fff-958e-a335-7abac1253f64"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;"><br></span></strong></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><strong style="font-weight:normal;" id="docs-internal-guid-4b9a4639-7fff-958e-a335-7abac1253f64"></strong><br></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;"><strong>Food Options</strong></span></p><p><strong style="font-weight:normal;" id="docs-internal-guid-4b9a4639-7fff-958e-a335-7abac1253f64"><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><br></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 11pt;">There are a handful of restaurants open year-round in the Village, including the Latitude 62, Denali Brew Pub, Conscious Coffee, Mountain High Pizza Pie, the West Rib, and the Roadhouse Bakery. The summer season has a plethora of food trucks and pop-up eateries, ranging from the Salmon Spot to the Talkeetna Spinach Bread cutie Airstream, Breakfast Candy, Mountain BBQ, the Burger Barn, and the Homestead Kitchen. There is also Nagleys General Store that stocks food essentials, ice cream, and coffee, and a liquor store. They are open daily. And no visit to Talkeetna would be complete without dropping into the 100-year-old Fairview Inn for a drink and watching the Supercubs take off overhead from the Village Airstrip.</span></p></strong></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><br class="Apple-interchange-newline"><p><br></p>',
